    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-10-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-10-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="264"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d264">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/581.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-10-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 17, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your October 14. The rebellion not anti foreign. Rebels as well as loyalists
                    disposed to protect foreigners. Except from Hankow and vicinity there seems to
                    be no need for removal of Americans. Steady movement of troops southward.
                    Russians have ordered troops to Suppress Hunghutzus in Manchuria.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Williams.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
